snippet.title: Amber Heard 'invented' Kate Moss 'rumour' 'out of spite', court hears
snippet.description: Amber Heard has been accused of "inventing" a rumour that  pushed his ex-girlfriend Kate Moss "down the stairs" into his libel trial in a "moment of unscripted malevolence".   Depp, 57, is suing News Group Newspapers for libel over a story published in The Sun in 201 which branded him a "wife beater" - an egation he vehemently denies.   The trial has reached day 16 and is expected to come to an end this afternoon.  Depp has denied ever being violent towards his ex-wife, and claimed it was Heard who was abusive towards him throughout their relationship.  The actor's lawyer, David Sherborne, began his closing statements and addressed the moment Heard dropped a bombshell claim about Depp's supermodel ex during her testimony.  He eged she deliberately threw the "rumour" into her testimony out of spite.  Sherborne said Heard "in yet another moment of unscripted malevolence" had "tossed in a detail" to say she had "remembered a rumour" that Depp had pushed Moss down the stairs.   He told th ...
